Russian foreign minister Sergei Lavrov called the scenes of dead civilians, discovered after Russian troops retreated from the area a "fake attack". Many of the bodies had their hands bound, had close-range gunshot wounds and displayed signs of torture. However, newly released satellite images show that the bodies had been lying in Bucha for weeks, with bodies clearly visible in footage from March 19, thus disproving Moscow's claims. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...